@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

title The Four Physical Bottlenecks

top to bottom direction

rectangle "Same Queueing Law\nL = lambda x W" as law #E6F3FF

rectangle "CPU\nCores and cycles\nWatch: run queue, CPU busy" as cpu #FFE6E6
rectangle "Memory\nCapacity and bandwidth\nWatch: reclaim, GC, swapping" as memory #E8F4FF
rectangle "Disk\nIOPS and throughput\nWatch: await, util, queue depth" as disk #FFF7CC
rectangle "Network\nBandwidth and latency\nWatch: drops, retransmits, buffer queues" as network #E6FFE6

cpu --> law : queued work
memory --> law : waiting on bytes
disk --> law : waiting on I/O
network --> law : waiting on packets

note bottom of law #FEFFDD
  Same pattern everywhere:
  as utilization approaches the service limit,
  queues grow and latency rises sharply.
end note

@enduml
